HEADWORD: Megasthene
<hw>Meg"as*thene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>me`gas</grk> great + <grk>sqe`nos</grk> strength.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a group which includes the higher orders
of mammals, having a large size as a typical characteristic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

